benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/admin/invoices - Trigger an invoice generation for all parked accounts

covered: POST Method - Valid Payload: Scenarios cover successful generation (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC10, TC12, TC13, TC16, TC17, TC18).
POST Method - Invalid Payload/Validation: Scenarios test missing required header, invalid parameter values, non-integer parameters (TC05, TC06, TC07).
Authorization - Proper handling: Tests for missing/invalid/expired tokens and unauthorized access (TC05, TC08).
Server/Dependency Availability: Tests for backend/service down and 503 response (TC09).
Pagination and Query Parameters: Tests for offset/limit, default behavior, and extra query parameters (TC01, TC02, TC11, TC13, TC10).
Auditing/Headers: Tests ensuring optional headers are recorded for auditing (TC03, TC16).
Edge Cases: Tests for no parked accounts, excessive dataset (TC04, TC12), extra query parameter handling (TC11).
Regression - backward compatibility and header parsing: Tests ensuring compatibility and header parsing correctness (TC16, TC17).
gaps: Duplicate Submission: No explicit test ensuring idempotency or handling of repeated submissions for the same accounts.
Caching Behavior: No tests checking ETag/Cache-Control or caching headers.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating rate limiting or throttling under burst requests.
Payload Validation Depth: Lack of explicit tests around the structure/content of the POST body beyond header/parameters (e.g., invalid JSON structure or unexpected body fields).
500 Internal Server Error: Only 503 service unavailability tested; add test for generic 500 scenarios.
Unknown/Unsupported Parameters Handling: TC11 allows 200 or 400 but does not specify deterministic behavior for unsupported parameters across all edge cases.
recommendations: Add an idempotency/duplicate submission test to verify that repeated POSTs do not generate invoices more than once for the same parked accounts.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior where applicable.
Add rate limiting tests to ensure system gracefully handles bursts (e.g., several concurrent requests per second).
Introduce explicit payload validation tests for the POST body structure (malformed JSON, extra unexpected fields) to ensure robust server-side validation.
Include a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to cover non-503 server failures and verify proper error handling.
Clarify and standardize behavior for unknown/unsupported query parameters across edge cases with deterministic outcomes (prefer 400 for invalid parameters).
